  "title": "Part-time Dietitian (West, 2 days per week)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Conduct individual nutrition assessments and formulate care plans based on clinical findings.</li>\n  <li>Deliver evidence-informed dietary guidance to patients and their families across various medical conditions.</li>\n  <li>Advise foodservice staff on therapeutic meal planning in accordance with medical directives.</li>\n  <li>Participate in collaborative care reviews and contribute to multidisciplinary treatment strategies.</li>\n  <li>Engage in research projects or clinical audits related to nutritional interventions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Recognized qualification in Dietetics (or equivalent) from a reputable institution.</li>\n  <li>Active member of a professional dietetics or nutrition association (e.g., SNDA or equivalent).</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of relevant experience working in <strong>hospital or clinical environments.</strong></li>\n  <li>Able to work autonomously with strong communication and collaboration skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
